    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/390</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8008. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Your 645, Embassy 10235, May 23, 8 p.m. You may include in letter of adhesion the
                    following relative to bunkering: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The War Trade Board during the currency of the above-mentioned agreement
                            will grant bunker licenses freely tor coal and oil and stores for
                            Swedish vessels operating as contemplated by the agreement.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>We suggest a clause in this connection requiring that there would be no lay-up of
                    Swedish steamers during the currency of the agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
